The Pentecost University College is a private university located at Sowutuom in the Greater Accra Region of Ghana. It is one of the new universities in Ghana and was granted accreditation by the National Accreditation Board in 1994.[1][2] It was established in March 2003 by the Church of Pentecost in Ghana.[2] The chairman of the Church of Pentecost is also the Chancellor of the university.[3] The university has had three faculties since 2005. [4] 
